=== Party Slot Structure ===

Each character has a 16-byte data block in RAM with the following layout:

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Offset !! Size !! Description !! Notes
|-
| +$00 || 1 || Character ID || $00-$07 for main, $c5-$cc for companions
|-
| +$01 || 2 || Current HP || Little-endian
|-
| +$03 || 1 || Current MP || Single byte (max 255)
|-
| +$04 || 1 || Strength || Base + equipment bonus
|-
| +$05 || 1 || Agility || Affects turn order
|-
| +$06 || 1 || Vitality || Defense calculation
|-
| +$07 || 1 || Intelligence || Spell power
|-
| +$08 || 1 || Luck || Critical/dodge
|-
| +$09 || 3 || Experience || 24-bit, little-endian
|-
| +$0c || 1 || Level || 1-99 range
|-
| +$0d || 1 || Status flags || Poison, sleep, etc.
|-
| +$0e || 2 || Max HP || Little-endian
|}

